# CODEOWNERS — review routing for the measured gate's trust-critical files.
# PROM16 P2 item 6 (cell B2): the mandated impact manifest is the trust root of
# the measured gate (docs/ADR-0003). A change to the manifest — or to the pinned
# impact tests it names, or to the gate/measurement code that interprets them —
# changes WHAT a green verdict means. CODEOWNERS requests the right review; actual
# merge enforcement requires a host ruleset/branch-protection rule that makes the
# review mandatory. The other half (a KG/CI manifest source) stays at the
# ManifestSource seam.
#
# The canonical repository owner is used because it is resolvable on this host.

# The manifest plus every project-controlled Python input that can affect the
# measured run. Directory scope includes package initializers, phase contracts,
# all tests, and any nested conftest.py added later.
/apt-impact.json          @gj3447
/src/apt_engine/          @gj3447
/tests/                   @gj3447

# Root-level pytest/build configuration and a future root conftest.py can alter
# collection, dependency installation, or outcomes, so they share the trust belt.
/conftest.py              @gj3447
/pyproject.toml           @gj3447
/pytest.ini               @gj3447
/setup.cfg                @gj3447
/setup.py                 @gj3447
/tox.ini                  @gj3447

# The trusted-runner workflow, structural boundary, and ownership map itself.
/.github/workflows/       @gj3447
/.importlinter            @gj3447
/CODEOWNERS               @gj3447
